<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>PE Fund Accounting Flow</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      margin: 20px;
      background: #f7f9fc;
    }
    h1, h2 { margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .step {
      background: white;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 16px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    }
    .flow {
      font-size: 24px;
      text-align: center;
      margin: 12px 0;
    }
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }
    th, td {
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      padding: 10px;
      text-align: left;
    }
    th {
      background: #eef3ff;
    }
    .dr { font-weight: bold; }
    .cr { font-weight: bold; }
    .note {
      margin-top: 10px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #555;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h1>Private Equity Fund Accounting Flow</h1>
  <p>Entry-level visual guide for fund administrator / intermediary accounting.</p>

  <div class="flow">
    Capital Call → Invest → Fair Value → Exit → Distribution
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <h2>1. Capital Call</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Debit</th><th>Credit</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="dr">Due from LPs</td><td class="cr">Partners' Capital</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="dr">Cash</td><td class="cr">Due from LPs</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="note">LPs commit cash to the fund.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <h2>2. Investment Purchase</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Debit</th><th>Credit</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="dr">Investment at Cost</td><td class="cr">Cash</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="note">Fund deploys investor capital.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <h2>3. Fair Value Adjustment</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Debit</th><th>Credit</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="dr">Investment</td><td class="cr">Unrealized Gain</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="note">Adjust investment to fair value.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <h2>4. Exit / Realized Gain</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Debit</th><th>Credit</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="dr">Cash</td><td class="cr">Investment</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="dr">Investment</td><td class="cr">Realized Gain</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="note">Investment is sold and gain/loss is recognized.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="step">
    <h2>5. Distribution / Return of Capital</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Debit</th><th>Credit</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="dr">Partners' Capital</td><td class="cr">Cash</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="note">Cash distributed back to investors.</div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
